  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The referral center for eating disorders provides for a systematic 4-year follow-up of&#xD;
      patients under care with an annual assessment at the center. The investigators have recently&#xD;
      shown the frequency of relapse in the first 7 years after diagnosis, but the literature&#xD;
      remains poor on this epidemiology and on the risk factors for relapse. The investigators&#xD;
      would therefore like to extend this follow-up for an additional 3 years with an annual&#xD;
      telephone nursing interview for all cured patients to cover the overall 7-year period.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
